<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A 17-year-old boy has tragically drowned at an unpatrolled beach on the New South Wales mid north coast. </p>

<p>The teenager got into difficulties while swimming with his family at Diamond Head, about 40km south of Port Macquarie at about 1pm on Wednesday.</p>

<p>Police pulled him from the water and started CPR, before paramedics arrived  on the scene and took over. </p>

<p>Sadly, he was unable to be revived and died at the scene.</p>

<p>A report will be prepared for the coroner. </p>
